column11: Moragahakanda DamÂ is a recent addition to Matale district and the main part of the Morgahakanda/Kaluganga project. It is the last of the Great Mahaveli project. The sad part was could not go near the dam and was viewed it from far. Officials do not allow to see this now. Very beautiful to the far.
Worth stopping for few mins if you are traveling on Naula  - Elahera road. View is super beautiful.  Surrounding area including the bordering mountain range creates a beautiful view.

column8: Newly built reservior of Sri Lanka
column11: This one of the largest reservoirs of Sri Lanka built recently. Moragahakanda Reservior can be approached from Naula (A9 road) as well as Polonnaruwa. Road conditions are excellent. There are two places to view the reservior: Moragahakanda dam view point and Moragahakanda reservior view point. The dam view point is opened only from 9am to 5pm but reservior view point is a road side attraction. A set of mountains of Knuckles massif is appeared beyond the dam to add the beauty to the view. Entrance free and there are food sellers at reservior view point.
This is a large dam filled with water use for multipurpose requirement including power genaration & agricultur. Its located in beautiful environment giving nice seanaris at the veiw point
